The paper discusses techniques for reducing near-duplicates in web page and image search results, file system synchronization, compression, and learning applications. These are all areas that fall under the umbrella of data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of hash functions and sampling techniques, which are common tools in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of weighted sets, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS, followed by cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DB, and cs.AI.
